        <updateDate>2022-03-03T17:30:36Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p>This bill requires the President to report to Congress a determination as to whether certain specified Russian persons meet the criteria to be subject to sanctions under the Global Magnitsky Human Rights Accountability Act. </p> <p>Russian persons specified in this bill include businessperson Roman Abramovich, Minister of Health Mikhail Murashko, and Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to require a review of sanctions with respect to Russian kleptocrats and human rights abusers.</title>
